<emphasis id="B922EAC3FFB35343255AF4F55FC1B01A" bold="true" box="[100,255,2898,2923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C564D52FFB353432430F4F55DA2B01A" authority="Fitzinger, 1867" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1867" box="[270,668,2898,2923]" class="Mammalia" family="Caviidae" genus="Cavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tschudii">Cavia tschudii Fitzinger, 1867</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B3E3C8CFFB353432792F4F55A2EB01A" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3784487318" box="[684,1296,2898,2923]" pageId="2" pageNumber="433">“in der Umgegend der Stadt Yca,” Ica, Peru</materialsCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C564D52FFB353432556F4D65E1DB0E3" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1867" box="[104,291,2929,2962]" class="Mammalia" family="Caviidae" genus="Cavia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="433" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tschudii">Cavia tschudii</taxonomicName>
is in need of revision relative to its subspecific taxonomy. A. Cabrera includes the subspecies umbrata as a synonym of festina and they have similar ranges. This is pending further review. Eight subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
